# 🧪 CODE MODE - VALIDATION RULES

**🚨 CRITICAL: Validation is MANDATORY after EVERY code change. NO EXCEPTIONS.**

## RULE CHAIN CONTEXT
- **Parent Rule**: `.cursor/rules/modes/code-mode.mdc` (Always Active in Code Mode)
- **Chained With**: `implementation.mdc`, testing rules
- **Active When**: Code Mode is active and ANY code change has been made

---

## MANDATORY VALIDATION PROTOCOL

### IMMEDIATE VALIDATION - AFTER EVERY CHANGE:
1. ✅ **SYNTAX VALIDATION** - Code MUST compile/parse without errors
2. ✅ **FUNCTIONAL VALIDATION** - Code MUST perform intended functionality
3. ✅ **INTEGRATION VALIDATION** - Code MUST work with existing system
4. ✅ **PERFORMANCE VALIDATION** - Code MUST NOT degrade performance
5. ✅ **SECURITY VALIDATION** - Code MUST follow security best practices

### VALIDATION FREQUENCY - ABSOLUTE REQUIREMENTS:
- 🚫 **NEVER proceed without validation** - Validate EVERY single change immediately
- ✅ **Before Mode Transition** - Complete comprehensive validation before handoff
- ✅ **Before User Feedback** - ALL changes MUST be validated before user review
- ✅ **Before Memory Updates** - Validate before updating `.memory/task_subtasks.md`

### VALIDATION EXECUTION METHODS

#### SYNTAX VALIDATION - MANDATORY FIRST STEP:
- ✅ **Run `pnpm test`** - Execute full test suite immediately after changes
- ✅ **TypeScript Compilation** - Verify all TypeScript compiles without errors
- ✅ **ESLint Validation** - Run `pnpm lint` to ensure code quality standards
- ✅ **Import Resolution** - Verify all imports resolve correctly
- 🚫 **NEVER run `pnpm dev` or `npm dev`** - User likely has development server running

#### FUNCTIONAL VALIDATION - VERIFY BEHAVIOR:
- ✅ **Manual Testing** - Physically test the implemented functionality in browser/app
- ✅ **Edge Case Testing** - Test boundary conditions and error scenarios
- ✅ **User Flow Testing** - Verify complete user workflows work end-to-end
- ✅ **API Testing** - Test all API endpoints and data flows if applicable

#### INTEGRATION VALIDATION - SYSTEM COHERENCE:
- ✅ **Component Integration** - Verify new code works with existing components
- ✅ **State Management** - Ensure state updates work correctly across the system
- ✅ **Route Testing** - Test navigation and routing if web application
- ✅ **Database Integration** - Verify database operations if applicable

#### PERFORMANCE VALIDATION - NO DEGRADATION:
- ✅ **Load Time Impact** - Measure page/component load time changes
- ✅ **Memory Usage** - Monitor for memory leaks or excessive usage
- ✅ **Bundle Size** - Check for significant bundle size increases
- ✅ **Runtime Performance** - Verify no performance regressions

#### SECURITY VALIDATION - PROTECTION MAINTAINED:
- ✅ **Input Sanitization** - Verify all user inputs are properly sanitized
- ✅ **Authentication** - Ensure access controls remain intact
- ✅ **Data Exposure** - Check for accidental data leaks or exposure
- ✅ **Dependency Security** - Verify no new security vulnerabilities introduced

